ODM national chairman John Mbadi has instructed Migori party officials to accept the office donation by Governor Okoth Obado.Obado has donated a new office and land to the party. He recently defected from PDP.&ldquo;If there is any donation do not reject it. Officials should sit down with Obado and see what can be done,&rdquo; Mbadi said.The Suba MP spoke in Awendo on Saturday during a funds drive.Earlier, Migori party officials led by chairman Philip Makabong&rsquo;o and secretary general Joseph Olala refused to accept the office, saying they will work from the ODM offices at county stadium.Mbadi said accepting the donation does not mean Obado will be favoured in the primaries